    {
      "paragraph_name": "FUNC-CODES",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data definition paragraph defines a set of constants representing IMS (Information Management System) function codes. These codes are used as parameters when calling IMS to perform specific database operations. The defined function codes include 'GU' (Get Unique), 'GHU' (Get Hold Unique), 'GN' (Get Next), 'GHN' (Get Hold Next), 'GNP' (Get Next within Parent), 'GHNP' (Get Hold Next within Parent), 'REPL' (Replace), 'ISRT' (Insert), and 'DLET' (Delete). Each function code is a 4-character alphanumeric field with a predefined value. These values are used to instruct IMS on the desired database action. The paragraph also defines PARMCOUNT which specifies the number of parameters expected by the IMS call.",
